(211, 2, '2007-12-11 16:25:40', '2007-12-11 23:25:40', 'Level 1 of the reverse hierarchy test.  This is to make sure the importer correctly assigns parents and children even when the children come first in the export file.', 'Level 1', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'level-1__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-18 17:27:45', '2017-05-18 17:27:45', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/level-1/', 5, 'page', '', 0),
(332, 6, '2014-02-20 10:56:55', '2014-02-20 10:56:55', '[caption id=\"attachment_333\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"224\"]<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/chris-on-slopes.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-333 \" alt=\"On the slopes in Verbier\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/chris-on-slopes-224x300.jpg\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" /></a> On the slopes in Verbier[/caption]\n<h1>Working hard is great, but you also need some time out!</h1>\nI\'m sure everyone can agree with me on this one? We all work hard and we all need to get away, whether that be on a family holiday, weekend away or simply some time at home, it\'s just as important as working hard. I can speak from experience on this one and can clearly remember being at University, doing 12 hour Ambulance shifts (as part of my placement) and running a business over 100 miles away... People kept telling me to take some time out, not least my family and it wasn\'t until they booked a family holiday for me, that I realised just how much I needed to get away for a break.\n\nIt is sometime hard to realise that you do need a break, you get so deep into what your doing and keeping up to speed with what\'s happening, whether you have reached your goals, monthly targets, ongoing projects - the list is endless.\n\nMy advice is simple and something I have been doing for the past couple of years - <strong>book breaks in advance!</strong>\n\n... This has reminded me to book some holidays!', 'Need a Holiday?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'need-holiday', '', '', '2014-02-20 10:56:55', '2014-02-20 10:56:55', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=332', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(358, 2, '2010-10-05 00:27:25', '2010-10-05 07:27:25', 'All children, except one, grow up. They soon know that they will grow up, and the way Wendy knew was this. One day when she was two years old she was playing in a garden, and she plucked another flower and ran with it to her mother. I suppose she must have looked rather delightful, for Mrs. Darling put her hand to her heart and cried, \"Oh, why can\'t you remain like this for ever!\" This was all that passed between them on the subject, but henceforth Wendy knew that she must grow up. You always know after you are two. Two is the beginning of the end.\n\n<!--more-->\n\nMrs. Darling first heard of Peter when she was tidying up her children\'s minds. It is the nightly custom of every good mother after her children are asleep to rummage in their minds and put things straight for next morning, repacking into their proper places the many articles that have wandered during the day.\n\nIf you could keep awake (but of course you can\'t) you would see your own mother doing this, and you would find it very interesting to watch her. It is quite like tidying up drawers. You would see her on her knees, I expect, lingering humorously over some of your contents, wondering where on earth you had picked this thing up, making discoveries sweet and not so sweet, pressing this to her cheek as if it were as nice as a kitten, and hurriedly stowing that out of sight. When you wake in the morning, the naughtiness and evil passions with which you went to bed have been folded up small and placed at the bottom of your mind and on the top, beautifully aired, are spread out your prettier thoughts, ready for you to put on.\n\nI don\'t know whether you have ever seen a map of a person\'s mind. Doctors sometimes draw maps of other parts of you, and your own map can become intensely interesting, but catch them trying to draw a map of a child\'s mind, which is not only confused, but keeps going round all the time. There are zigzag lines on it, just like your temperature on a card, and these are probably roads in the island, for the Neverland is always more or less an island, with astonishing splashes of colour here and there, and coral reefs and rakish-looking craft in the offing, and savages and lonely lairs, and gnomes who are mostly tailors, and caves through which a river runs, and princes with six elder brothers, and a hut fast going to decay, and one very small old lady with a hooked nose. It would be an easy map if that were all, but there is also first day at school, religion, fathers, the round pond, needle-work, murders, hangings, verbs that take the dative, chocolate pudding day, getting into braces, say ninety-nine, three-pence for pulling out your tooth yourself, and so on, and either these are part of the island or they are another map showing through, and it is all rather confusing, especially as nothing will stand still.\n\nOf course the Neverlands vary a good deal. John\'s, for instance, had a lagoon with flamingoes flying over it at which John was shooting, while Michael, who was very small, had a flamingo with lagoons flying over it. John lived in a boat turned upside down on the sands, Michael in a wigwam, Wendy in a house of leaves deftly sewn together. John had no friends, Michael had friends at night, Wendy had a pet wolf forsaken by its parents, but on the whole the Neverlands have a family resemblance, and if they stood still in a row you could say of them that they have each other\'s nose, and so forth. On these magic shores children at play are for ever beaching their coracles [simple boat]. We too have been there; we can still hear the sound of the surf, though we shall land no more.\n\nOf all delectable islands the Neverland is the snuggest and most compact, not large and sprawly, you know, with tedious distances between one adventure and another, but nicely crammed. When you play at it by day with the chairs and table-cloth, it is not in the least alarming, but in the two minutes before you go to sleep it becomes very real. That is why there are night-lights.\n\nOccasionally in her travels through her children\'s minds Mrs. Darling found things she could not understand, and of these quite the most perplexing was the word Peter. She knew of no Peter, and yet he was here and there in John and Michael\'s minds, while Wendy\'s began to be scrawled all over with him. The name stood out in bolder letters than any of the other words, and as Mrs. Darling gazed she felt that it had an oddly cocky appearance.', 'Post Format: Standard', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-standard__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:10', '2017-05-19 10:12:10', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=358', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(385, 6, '2014-02-20 12:34:46', '2014-02-20 12:34:46', '<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/jet.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-386 alignright\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/jet-300x229.png\" alt=\"jet\" width=\"300\" height=\"229\" /></a>I have always wanted to go on my own Private Jet, but I didn\'t think it would be at the age of 22, wearing my Paramedic uniform...</h2>\nMy team and I at <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> are used to medical repatriations, normally theses are performed for an array of insurance companies and take place in private aircraft or commercial flights with medical escort. However, just a few days after new year the operations team at Jigsaw Medical took a phone call from a private patient who was ill abroad and without travel insurance. The prospective client enquired about our <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/emergency-ambulance-service.html\">medical repatriation</a> services and whether we could help get her home for medical treatment in the UK…\n\nNormally our \"Private Jets\" are old propeller aircraft specifically used for air repatriations and therefore not really that glamorous... However for this job (due to the lack of insurance) we had to charter a \'normal\' private jet from our friends at <a href=\"http://www.saxonair.com/\">Saxon Air.</a>\n\nObviously, as the \'boss\' and a Paramedic myself, it was left to me to carry out this job (along with a colleague Kathryn, who is also a Paramedic). Believe it or not, <strong>it was cheaper to get a private jet</strong> than it would have been to drive by land ambulance.\n<h3>In just under 3 hours, our shift on our RRV (or plane) was done and the patient was successfully back in a UK hospital!</h3>', 'My Day out in a Private Jet', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'day-private-jet', '', '', '2014-02-20 12:34:46', '2014-02-20 12:34:46', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=385', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(404, 6, '2014-02-20 14:16:58', '2014-02-20 14:16:58', '[caption id=\"attachment_405\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/beanbag-room.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-405 \" alt=\"beanbag-room\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/beanbag-room-300x224.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /></a> My thinking room @ Jigsaw House[/caption]\n<h3>I for one would love to grow my businesses as quickly as possible... but you can\'t afford to run out of money...</h3>\nThis is a question I have asked myself a number of times and have often discussed with my family and friends. The reality is, nobody seems to know the definitive answer but I can say - its a very important factor. I used to not worry about cash flow at all and just deal with it as the issues arose, however our ethos as a business is to pay our bills on time and get paid on time (easier said than done!). I am very lucky to have a supportive family and a supportive bank manager - all of which help when it comes to cash flow.\n\nGrowth of a business and its cash flow go hand-in-hand, good businesses grow when they have lots of cash; through investing in their workforce, assets and processes (and of course they stop when they don\'t have any free cash!). However, not-so-good businesses will pay their shareholders handsomely and not re-invest. <strong>No investment = No growth.</strong>\n\nI will always remember learning my lesson in cash flow, I clearly remember my dad telling me not to buy some new equipment (which was not vital) as I would <em>\"run out of money\"</em>... and guess what happened. Since then, we keep a close eye on our cash flow in both businesses, our accountant sits in our main office which really helps when it comes to keeping on top of the finances, but best of all Abi (my Sales Manager) sits opposite me and keeps an even closer eye on spending (she is from Yorkshire)!\n<h2>So whats the answer?</h2>\nPlan to grow when you have plenty of cash in the bank, not when you do not. Be strategic in the growth and <strong><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/dont-become-busy-fools/\">don\'t become busy fools</a>.</strong>\n<h2></h2>', 'How fast should you grow your business?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'fast-grow-business', '', '', '2014-02-20 14:16:58', '2014-02-20 14:16:58', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=404', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(418, 6, '2014-02-20 14:46:18', '2014-02-20 14:46:18', '<h1><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/8-arm-salesman.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-419 alignright\" alt=\"Travailler plus...\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/8-arm-salesman-300x271.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"271\" /></a>I meet a lot of busy fools in business, most of them are our competitors in <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a>! But what is a busy fool and how can you avoid becoming one of them...</h1>\nThere are so many opportunities to be a busy fool in today’s business environment, if you can relate to this - perhaps now is a great time to give yourself a shake and set some New Year’s resolutions to ensure you drop the “fool” and just stay busy....\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Saying \"YES!\"</span></h2>\nRichard Branson is known as \"Mr Yes\" at <a href=\"http://www.virgin.com/\">Virgin</a> and although I agree there is a lot to be said about saying \'Yes\' (and I do this myself most of the time), you also need to know when to say NO! This is more relevent when it comes to business and I can best relate to this in our work with Jigsaw Medical and <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/event-medical-cover.html\">event medical cover</a>. The event cover industry is full of \'cheap and cheerful companies\' which we do not compete with at Jigsaw Medical, we stick to what we are good at - at the higher end of the spectrum, motor sport, festivals and the like. We used to say Yes to everyone - and guess what we became...\n<h3>... Make sure you find your niche and stick to it.</h3>', 'Don\'t become \'busy fools\'', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dont-become-busy-fools', '', '', '2014-02-20 14:46:18', '2014-02-20 14:46:18', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=418', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(423, 6, '2014-02-20 15:59:10', '2014-02-20 15:59:10', '<h1><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/map_of_the_internet_by_tophthetomboy-d348wf0.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-424 alignleft\" alt=\"map_of_the_internet_by_tophthetomboy-d348wf0\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/map_of_the_internet_by_tophthetomboy-d348wf0-300x165.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"165\" /></a>What\'s this? The internet?</h1>\nCompanies large and small are getting used to fact that you <strong>need</strong> to have a web site. But just having a web site doesn\'t guarantee a company an increase in business--if those millions of potential customers don\'t happen to stumble on it, you\'re spinning your virtual wheels... Obviously with <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk\">eJigsaw</a> you will have gathered that I love the internet and realising its potential to our businesses. Although I am a believer that businesses can survive without a website, its only a small number of sectors where this is possible. The recent Google advert very powerfully re-enforced the power of the internet and a fantastic <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/website-design-chester/\">website design</a>.\n<h2>The search engines</h2>\nThose of you who know what we do at eJigsaw and what has partially made the success of Jigsaw Medical so far is that we have some very powerful search engine marketing, which is all ethical, organic and in-house. For example, our Jigsaw Medical website is optimised by our friends at eJigsaw for many search terms, including <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">first aid training</a>. When we talk about businesses surviving without an internet presence, I strongly feel that without our websites, social media and range of internet marketing streams - we would not be where we are today.\n<h2>What do you need to see a return from your online investment?</h2>\nObviously we would be bias in who you should use to provide this service to your business, because I think the team at eJigsaw would take some beating! But from a personal point of view, you need to look at building your online presence by using the following tips!\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>A great website design - </strong>This is the fundamental part of your internet presence, its your online office, just think of it as your house, but online.</li>\n	<li><strong>Search engine marketing</strong> - Once you have a great website for your business, it needs to be found by these millions of potential customers, having a great SEO company will help you get found on Google and other search engines.</li>\n	<li><strong>Branding -</strong> Your website and everything you do should be focused around your brand!</li>\n	<li><strong>Social Media -</strong> You need to be on Twitter, Facebook Business and Google + (at the least)</li>\n	<li><strong>Active Blog</strong> - Make sure you have an active blog which is interesting (unlike mine) and provides a growth in your website content.</li>\n	<li><strong>DELEGATE</strong> - Do not spend to much time trying to do this yourself - Hire <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/\">eJigsaw</a>!</li>\n</ol>', 'Making money from your online presence', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'making-money-online-presence', '', '', '2014-02-20 15:59:10', '2014-02-20 15:59:10', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=423', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(430, 6, '2014-02-21 11:12:43', '2014-02-21 11:12:43', '<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\"The right people for your business are those who can do their job when they don’t feel like it. The wrong people are those who can’t do their job when they do feel like it.\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/person-with-question-mark-backgrounds-wallpapers.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-431 alignleft\" alt=\"person-with-question-mark-backgrounds-wallpapers\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/person-with-question-mark-backgrounds-wallpapers-300x198.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"198\" /></a></h2>\n<h2>Getting the right people, at the right time, into the right positions within your organisation, is critical to it\'s success...</h2>\nI am strong believer that it is the people who make a business good, or bad. I recently made one of our suppliers an ex-supplier, as I felt their customer service ethos was not in line with what we expect as a customer, but I also didn\'t want them to be an instrumental part of our business. In the same token, because it\'s the people who make your business, it\'s also the people who make (or break) theirs. In my view suppliers and customers should be treated in the same way, we need both of them to provide an excellent service to our clients, if someone in their business letting that down - we would go elsewhere. The same can be said for our businesses, if <em>people</em> don\'t like our <em>people</em>, this will reflect badly on our business - however good we may be.... <strong>you might be getting the drift about the whole \'people\' thing!</strong>\n<h2>Customer service</h2>\n<strong>Not everyone will be great at dealing with customers</strong>, <strong>but that\'s okay providing that is not their role!</strong><strong> </strong>Getting the right people in the right place is the aim of the game, those who are customer facing should be organised, approachable, problem solving and have a passion for great customer service. For example, in <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> our clinicains need to be skilled, professional and naturally caring, but also our design team in <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/\">eJigsaw</a> also need to be skilled, professional and caring. Lots of core attributes will transfer over - whatever the role!\n<h2></h2>\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/job-interview-answers-questions.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-436 alignright\" alt=\"job-interview-answers-questions\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/job-interview-answers-questions-300x196.jpg\" width=\"209\" height=\"136\" /></a></h2>\n<h2>How to get the right people...</h2>\nNow there is a question... I\'m confident that nobody would actually know the answer to this one (I\'m just 22 but have already had to \"restructure\" one of my organisation\'s to ensure we maintained the right people, in the right places).... But here are some top-tips!\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Use a professional HR company</strong> to help with the nitty gritty - we use <a href=\"https://www.peninsula-online.com/\">Peninsula Business Services </a>in all of our businesses, they are friendly, realistic and professional</li>\n	<li><strong>Use Psychometric profiling</strong> to uncover the \'real\' person behind the interview - we use <a href=\"http://yenomassociates.co.uk/\">Yenom Associates</a> for all of our Occupational Personality Profiling (OPP)</li>\n	<li><strong>Take your time</strong> in choosing the right person, they may not be the first person you meet or interview, but they may be filling in your online application!</li>\n	<li><strong>Don\'t use recruitment agencies </strong>for permanent positions - there are some exceptions to this rule, but generally <strong>you</strong> know who you want on <strong>your</strong> <strong>team</strong>!</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Remember! The people you employ will almost certainly be the difference between success, and failure... but also the difference between an energetic and positive working life - or a hard one!</h2>', 'The right people in your business', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'right-people-business', '', '', '2014-02-21 11:12:43', '2014-02-21 11:12:43', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=430', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(444, 6, '2014-02-22 11:42:14', '2014-02-22 11:42:14', '<h3>Following on from my Blog post yesterday regarding having <a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/right-people-business/\">the right people in your business</a>, I found a great info-graphic from Plantronics, explaining more...</h3>\n<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/secret-keeping-employees-happy.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-445\" alt=\"secret-keeping-employees-happy\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/secret-keeping-employees-happy.jpg\" width=\"610\" height=\"2256\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>', 'Keeping employees happy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'keeping-employees-happy', '', '', '2014-02-22 11:42:14', '2014-02-22 11:42:14', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=444', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(448, 6, '2014-03-04 16:21:37', '2014-03-04 16:21:37', '[caption id=\"attachment_451\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"351\"]<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/look-at-competitors.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-451 \" alt=\"Don\'t spend all of your time spying...\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/look-at-competitors.jpg\" width=\"351\" height=\"359\" /></a> Don\'t spend all of your time spying...[/caption]\n<h1>If you concentrate more on what your competitors are doing, your own business will <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">fail</span>.</h1>\n<h3>... A bold claim, but one which I genuinely do believe in.</h3>\nThere is a small flip side to this which is that it is important to know what they are doing, but like everything - there is a limit to how much snooping you need to do! I am fairly confident I <strong>know</strong> exactly what our competitors in <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> and <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/\">eJigsaw</a> are doing, but I do not spend time <strong>concentrating</strong> on what they are doing, or worse, \'spying\' on them. This is the important difference which you need to keep an eye on...\n<h3>Do you look at your competitors Facebook, website or twitter etc EACH DAY?</h3>\nIf your answer is yes, then to be brutally honest, you need to have a look at your own Facebook, twitter and concentrate on that! Don\'t get me wrong, a quarterly look at what they are up to - or even a reactive snoop is not a problem and, like I say, <strong>knowing</strong> what they are up to is important, <strong>concentrating</strong> on them is likely to put your own business onto the path of failure.\n<h3>So, what\'s the problem?</h3>\nThere are a few problems really, the main one being your lack of focus and effort on your own business - which should worry you. But other issues in concentrating too much on your competitors may also be the decrease in morale for yourself, and your team. By all means if they do something you think is great - make it better, don\'t copy it and start a \'cat fight\' - work with your team, your brand and your business - and make it better!\n<h3>How do you know?</h3>\nGood question - well I may only be 22 years-old, but already I have learnt this important lesson. I employed a manager in one of our divisions who was fixated on our competitors, he would text me, call me and email me about what they were up to and why... He would create negativity in the team by telling them all about how our competitors are doing this, and that - He was not looking closer to home at what <strong>we</strong> could do to make our service better and ultimately make them suffer. Needless to say, the person in question is no longer in my team..\n<h3>And guess what - we focused on us and <em>\'kept an eye\' on what they were up to</em> -<em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> not the other way round</span>.</em></h3>\n<h3>The end result = We doubled our turnover in that division &amp; lesson learnt!</h3>', 'Concentrate on your business, not your competitors', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'concentrate-on-you', '', '', '2014-03-04 16:21:37', '2014-03-04 16:21:37', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=448', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(460, 6, '2014-03-10 08:05:41', '2014-03-10 08:05:41', '<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/image.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-461 alignright\" alt=\"image\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/image.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"239\" /></a>You should have goals, whether they are just a goal for Monday,a goal for the month or a goal further ahead... You need them.\n\nI am a keen believer in goals and lining up a target, this goes for business and also personally. My business goals come in all shapes and sizes and focus on different aspects of my businesses.\n<h2>Tell your team</h2>\nDon\'t forget - if your goal involves your team (which I\'m sure it will), you need to share it with them, so they can also focus on helping you reach it!\n\nDon\'t just keep it to yourself!\n<h3>Have a Happy Monday and get some goals set!</h3>', 'What\'s your Goal?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'whats-goal', '', '', '2014-03-10 08:05:41', '2014-03-10 08:05:41', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=460', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(464, 6, '2014-03-22 09:42:02', '2014-03-22 09:42:02', 'I often see startup businesses and I sometimes think they have missed the point somewhere. Copying an existing business will not work - unless you take the bits they are not doing well at, and make them better in your business.\n\nThere are thousands of event medical and first aid training providers in the UK, there are also thousands of design &amp; hosting companies in the UK, so why are we succeeding? We have simply taken what the industry doesn\'t do very well, and made it 10 times better.\n\nSo my Saturday tip is this.... Don\'t just copy someone else\'s idea, take the industry by the reins, and <strong>make it better! </strong>\n\nRemember: \"it\'s about being different\"', 'Don\'t just copy...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'find-gap', '', '', '2014-03-22 09:42:02', '2014-03-22 09:42:02', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=464', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(475, 6, '2014-03-31 08:45:20', '2014-03-31 08:45:20', '<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/eJigsaw-Cloud.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-474 alignright\" alt=\"eJigsaw-Cloud\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/eJigsaw-Cloud.png\" width=\"328\" height=\"195\" /></a>The term “<strong>Cloud Computing</strong>” has become quite a perplexing and mystical phrase for many people. A lot of entrepreneurs know they should be looking into what the cloud can do for their company but aren’t certain of where to begin. If you’re struggling to get your head around what <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/cloud-hosting/\">cloud computing</a> actually is, then check out our website for <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/\">eJigsaw</a>....\n\nThe market over the next 5 years will change dramatically as the scepticism and concerns over moving to the cloud reduce and more and more people and businesses embrace the technology. Evidence suggests that the global cloud market could reach £150 billion by 2020<strong>.</strong> <strong></strong>\n\nFirstly entrepreneurs need a product that specifically meets their business needs – At eJigsaw we have invested a lot of our resources into creating a great value product that meets the needs of our direct customers, many of whom are entrepreneurs. The result is our market leading <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/cloud-hosting/\">Cloud Server</a> range.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/cloud-computing-datatrend.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-478 alignleft\" alt=\"cloud-computing-datatrend\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/cloud-computing-datatrend.jpg\" width=\"223\" height=\"167\" /></a>In my businesses, I want to keep overheads down, yet have the right solution to grow my business. In-house IT is extreemly expensive, especially when you are growing. Do you order the £10,000 server for today or the £15,000 as your growing, and may need this capacity tomorrow. Cloud hosting lets easily alter the capacity of your servers to meet the changing needs of your businesses. For instance, businesses with websites on cloud servers can schedule upgrades to cope with peaks in traffic. This ensures sites don’t go down or suffer from poor performance when they’re busy... When was the last time you saw \'Dragons Den\' and Googled the company who was pitching, only to find their website was \'down\'? It always confuses me (and I do often email them or even Tweet them) to promote our solid hosting services at <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk\">eJigsaw</a>. Its most likely the best advertising they will ever get and nobody can see their website!...\n<h3>Hosting is important, not least for entrepreneurs... so get yourself in The eJigsaw Cloud and <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/contact\">contact</a> my awesome hosting team today and keep your business online!</h3>', 'Cloud Computing for Entrepreneurs & Your Business', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cloud-computing-entrepreneurs-business', '', '', '2014-03-31 08:45:20', '2014-03-31 08:45:20', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=475', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(481, 6, '2014-04-01 11:18:50', '2014-04-01 11:18:50', '<h2>...Okay, this may turn into a slightly controversial post - so I will keep it brief and put it out there...</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/r-ONTARIO-TEACHERS-STRIKE-large570.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-482 alignright\" alt=\"r-ONTARIO-TEACHERS-STRIKE-large570\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/r-ONTARIO-TEACHERS-STRIKE-large570.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"167\" /></a>Does striking get you anywhere? - that\'s the question!\n\nWhen I was a student Paramedic, it was clear to me that unions sill very much existed and were campaigning for people to join up (for the record, I didn\'t as I personally don\'t believe in them). I am not convinced that striking is the way to be heard, its certainly the way to get some (bad) press and upset the nation, but I don\'t think its the way to put your point across in modern times.\n\nMost recently we saw teachers strike to get their views heard and whilst I agree with what they are saying, I still feel that people should find an alternative way to get their own way! Putting the education of the nations children at risk by doing it - is probably not the most favored move!\n<h3>Whats the alternative?</h3>\nIf a member of my team were to be upset or even close to thinking about \'striking\' I would be upset that they haven\'t approached me to discuss it... It\'s a little different in the fact that my team is small compared with the nations teachers! However, there is always someones office door you can knock on to get your opinions heard, without the banner printing costs and disruption!\n\nStriking often results in more harm than good and I think that\'s whats happened in the latest teaching strike. There’s got to be a better way to get the opinions of both sides heard and resolved, rather than neglecting the education of our young people<strong>.. We are all human after all!</strong> <strong></strong>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Let\'s Strike!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lets-strike', '', '', '2014-04-01 11:18:50', '2014-04-01 11:18:50', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=481', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(485, 6, '2014-04-01 16:33:32', '2014-04-01 16:33:32', '<strong><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/teamwork.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-486 alignright\" alt=\"teamwork\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/teamwork.png\" width=\"434\" height=\"261\" /></a>1. Lead with Enthusiasm &amp; Optimism</strong> – Negativity and fear are likely knocking your team off balance and it’s time to regroup, refocus, and unite to create a winning mindset, culture and positive team environment. Now, more than ever, is a time for positive leadership. Now is the time to uplift, encourage and inspire your teams. When your folks talk about the challenges, you talk about the opportunities. When others talk about why they can’t succeed, you give them every reason why they can. So often the difference between success and failure is belief and as a positive leader you need to inspire this belief and optimism in your team.\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>2. Don\'t Just Hide in Your Office</strong> – You need to be humble and hungry. Humble in that you seek to learn, grow, and improve every day, and hungry with a passion to work harder than everyone else. Now is not a time to be barricaded in your office. Now is a time to be in their with your team, leading, working, and building a successful future.</p>\n<strong>3. Set Goals &amp; Share Them</strong> – You should have goals, whether they are just a goal for Monday, a goal for the month or a goal further ahead… You need them. I am a keen believer in goals and lining up a target, this goes for business and also personally. My business goals come in all shapes and sizes and focus on different aspects of my businesses. Don’t forget – if your goal involves your team (which it will), you need to share it with them, so they can also focus on helping you reach it!\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>4. Share a Positive Vision</strong> – Rally your team around a positive vision for the road ahead. Instead of being disappointed about where you are, decide to be optimistic about where you are going. Vision helps you and your team see the road ahead and it gives you something meaningful and valuable to strive towards. Discuss where you have been, where you are going and why you are going there. Martin Luther King Jr. had a dream/vision and he changed the world with it. Share your dream and improve your organization with it. After all, if you think your best days are behind you, they are. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">If you think your best days are ahead of you, they are.</span></p>\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>5. Teach Your Team to Be Heroes, Not Victims</strong> – Heroes and victims get knocked down. The distinction between the two groups lies in the fact that heroes get back up while victims simply give up. Help your team to realise that they are not victims of circumstance. Rather, remind them that they have a high level of control—in other words, they have a significant influence over how things turn out - because they should!. Life is a story, and the story we tell ourselves and the role we play determines the quality and direction of our life. The most successful people and teams are able to overcome adversity by telling themselves a more positive story than the rest.</p>', '5 Ways to Motivate Your Team', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-ways-motivate-team', '', '', '2014-04-01 16:33:32', '2014-04-01 16:33:32', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=485', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(490, 6, '2014-04-10 11:30:20', '2014-04-10 11:30:20', '<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/business-plan-xs.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-491 alignright\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/business-plan-xs.jpg\" alt=\"Business plan\" width=\"467\" height=\"310\" /></a>Instead of waiting for someone else to hire you, why not set up a company and employ yourself?</h2>\nIt would be reasonable to say that starting your own business is not for everyone... it involves a great deal of hard work and risk, but also a massive potential reward. Many people who are looking at starting their own business really don\'t know where to begin. There is some guidence on the internet for you, including some help from the government on \'<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/starting-up-a-business/start-with-an-idea\">Starting your own business</a>\'.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>But here are my four (and a bit) top tips...</strong></span>\n\n<strong>1. A bad time is the right time... </strong>It is tricky to start a business at any time - not just during a recession - but their particular business idea is so niche, so focussed, and so special that they shrug off the gloom and just get on with it. The upside of starting a business during a downturn is that things can only get better as the economic climate improves, and you will have learnt an awful lot in the difficult times that you can use in the easier ones.\n\n<strong>2. The right idea... </strong>For those of you who have seen <a href=\"http://www.ejigsaw.co.uk/\">eJigsaw</a> - \"it\'s about being different\". Your idea either needs to be unique or something which is different from your prospective competitors, don\'t just copy someone else - do a better job!\n\n<strong>3. The tools... </strong>Most homes and most students are already equipped with quite a lot of the tools any business needs to reach a worldwide audience from day one. Computer power is so cheap that many school or university leavers have their own machines, with processing power unimaginable a few years ago. Laptops can edit sound or movies, design software, and keep track of all the details of a start-up business at minimal cost. Internet connectivity allows a start-up entrepreneur to collaborate with video conferencing at almost no cost, an extraordinary breakthrough.\n\n<strong>4. The people... </strong>Okay, it will not matter immediately (unless you are employing someone immediately) - but don\'t forget that people make a massive difference to your business and its success. Have the right people in your team and work with the best suppliers and support networks to make it easier for you and better for you business!\n\n<strong>... OH! And don\'t forget \'cash is king\', make sure you keep an eye on that cash flow! Have a look at my blog on <a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/fast-grow-business/\">\'how quick should you grow your business\'</a>\n</strong>', 'Starting Out In Business', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'starting-business', '', '', '2014-04-10 11:30:20', '2014-04-10 11:30:20', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=490', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(497, 6, '2014-06-20 06:56:38', '2014-06-20 06:56:38', 'I recently hit a big milestone in my journey so far, something which I didn\'t see happening so quickly...\n\nI was once told that there \'was no money in our industry\', I was told this by a chap who ended up selling me his business - and in the year following our acquisition we managed to double its revenue... I suppose that alone refuted his comment and made me more confident than ever that there was huge potential for a professional and forward thinking business in the sector.\n\nRecently however we have reached this milestone which I am very proud of along with the whole team - we were honoured to be asked to provide services for one of the worlds largest sporting events. Not only is this prestigious, it\'s also a single weekend contract which will see a turnover more than 2.5 times that seen in a whole year of this chaps company (before we bought it) - the same chap who told me some \"wise words\" and claimed there was no money in it.\n\nWas he right? ....Well yes, there was no money in it for him, or his ethos. But it goes to show that a company with the right ethos and people can make it happen in a very short space of time...\n\nSo some wise words for today - \"If you think you won\'t or you think you will, you\'re right - so be positive, change &amp; make it happen!\"', 'A Big Milestone...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'big-milestone', '', '', '2014-06-20 06:56:38', '2014-06-20 06:56:38', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=497', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(501, 2, '2010-08-01 09:42:26', '2010-08-01 16:42:26', 'The last item in this page\'s content is a floated image. Make sure any elements after it are clearing properly.\n\n<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-827\" title=\"Camera\" src=\"http://wpthemetestdata.files.wordpress.com/2010/08/manhattansummer.jpg?w=150\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"112\" />', 'Clearing Floats', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'clearing-floats__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-18 17:27:44', '2017-05-18 17:27:44', '', 202, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/', 2, 'page', '', 0),
(505, 6, '2014-06-28 14:05:06', '2014-06-28 14:05:06', '<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Mark-Zuckerberg.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-506 alignright\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Mark-Zuckerberg.jpg\" alt=\"Mark Zuckerberg\" width=\"314\" height=\"188\" /></a>It\'s a comment often made to \'young entrepreneurs\' and one which I am sometimes confused by (maybe I am too young to understand!?)... <strong>But.... \"What has age got to do with it?\"</strong>\n\nIt\'s unusual for people to make age-related comments to my face, but it\'s a comment often filtered back to me from those who work for, or simply support the businesses. The normal suspects are competitors (that\'s to be expected) and skeptics of some degree, but what has age actually got to do with it?\n\nMost people know of Mark Zuckerberg, who together with his college roommates and fellow Harvard University students, launched Facebook from his dormitory room.The group then introduced Facebook onto other campuses nationwide. In 2007, at the <strong>age of 23</strong>, Zuckerberg became a billionaire as a result of Facebook\'s success. Mark is now a 30 year old Billionaire and is still heavily involved in Facebook to this day...\n\nI am not afraid of telling people that I have a huge amount of support in place from family and friends, not to mention to team who I work with (which was also the case for the Mark Zuckerberg\'s of this world). Age has absolutely no correlation with how well someone is able to do a job, or indeed run a business. Do you think I do everything myself? of course not... The key is to employ people who are better than you at a particular function and encourage them to succeed - you cannot be good at everything and strategically leading a business is a skill in itself.\n\nInterestingly, one person who commented \"I was too young to run a business which deals with peoples lives\" is an <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">ex-policeman</span>! not a Doctor, not a Paramedic... So is a company like ours, ran by a registered Paramedic (that would be me) and clinically led by a highly experienced air ambulance Doctor not more appropriate than one ran by an <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">ex-policeman</span>? - This is down to experience, not Age! There are plenty of 22 year old Paramedics on emergency ambulances up and down the country, clinically responsible for patients... so why can\'t they run a business?\n\nWhat I would say is this... If you are young and run a business, employ people who can compliment your enthusiasm and experience, with theirs. Earn respect from them and be part of the team.', 'What has age got to do with it?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'age-got', '', '', '2014-06-28 14:05:06', '2014-06-28 14:05:06', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=505', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(515, 6, '2014-08-13 19:20:25', '2014-08-13 19:20:25', '<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/event-photographer-virgin-start-ups-04.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-516 alignright\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/event-photographer-virgin-start-ups-04.jpg\" alt=\"Virgin Start Ups Launch\" width=\"191\" height=\"127\" /></a>I am proud to have been accepted as a mentor for Virgin Startup, providing support and guidance for new entrepreneurs. Virgin StartUp is a not-for-profit organisation that helps entrepreneurs with the funding, resources and advice they need to make their business idea a reality.\n\nMy role is all about guidance and and helping entrepreneurs to achieve their goals and realise their potential. Help them understand problems, identify solutions and implement their plans. It is about sharing my experiences with them and provide a helping hand when required.\n<h2>About Virgin Startup</h2>\nOur main focus is to help you get the support you need to turn your great idea in to a successful and sustainable business.\n\nIf you are over 18 and a British citizen or legal UK resident who wants to start or expand a new business that’s less than a year old in England then you may be eligible for a start-up loan.\n\nWe will help you develop your business plan and your application for funding. Our business advisors will help you with your marketing plans and financial projections.\n\nIf you are successful in securing your small business funding we will continue to provide you with support in the form of training, workshops, master classes, peer-to-peer networking and one-to-one mentoring.\n\nVirgin StartUp has developed a mentoring platform to help match you with an experienced business mentor, both in the short and long term.\n<h3>You never know - I might just be your mentor....</h3>', 'Virgin Startup', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'virgin-startup', '', '', '2014-08-13 19:20:25', '2014-08-13 19:20:25', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=515', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(521, 6, '2014-09-07 08:45:52', '2014-09-07 08:45:52', '<h3></h3>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Screen-Shot-2014-09-07-at-09.40.07.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-522 alignright\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Screen-Shot-2014-09-07-at-09.40.07.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2014-09-07 at 09.40.07\" width=\"331\" height=\"178\" /></a>I recently received a very nice phone call from <a href=\"http://www.lloydsbankenterpriseawards.com/\">Lloyds Bank Enterprise Awards</a> with news that we have reached the Semi-Finals!</h3>\n<div id=\"stcpDiv\">The panel of experts from Lloyds Bank have shortlisted up to ten entries from <a href=\"http://www.lloydsbankenterpriseawards.com/how-the-awards-work/#regions-table\">each of the five heats</a>. <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> is proud to be one of those shortlisted businesses!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div id=\"stcpDiv\">Shortlisted businesses will give a pitch about their company to a <a href=\"http://www.lloydsbankenterpriseawards.com/judges/\">panel of judges</a>, followed by a question and answer session. A Best Start-up, Best Enterprise and Best Digital winner will be selected at each heat to go through to the final. We have been selected into the category of \'Best Enterprise\' and on the 16th September I will present our business to the panel of judges.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>We are very fortunate as a business to have very stable finances, but the £50,000 investment (should we win overall) would be well invested into cutting edge compliance and CRM software for our recruitment and clinical divisions.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>We are very proud to have got this far!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>See the shortlist <a href=\"http://www.lloydsbankenterpriseawards.com/latest/shortlisted.html\">here</a></div>\n</div>', 'We\'re In! Lloyds Bank Enterprise Awards...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lloyds-bank-enterprise-awards', '', '', '2014-09-07 08:45:52', '2014-09-07 08:45:52', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=521', 0, 'post', '', 0);
