(525, 6, '2014-09-07 14:06:44', '2014-09-07 14:06:44', '<h2>Those of you who have been following our progress in <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> for a while will know that our Clinical &amp; Training divisions are growing sustainably, but fast!</h2>\n[caption id=\"attachment_526\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/RB.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-526 \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/RB-300x168.jpg\" alt=\"Richard Branson, Kathryn Telford (Jigsaw Paramedic) and Sam Branson\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\" /></a> Richard Branson, Kathryn Telford (Jigsaw Paramedic) and Sam Branson[/caption]\n\nIf you told me 12 months ago that we would be sponsoring the Virgin STRIVE Challenge, providing a medical team from the o2 Arena to the top of the Mattahorn in Swizerland... and end up with a photograph with Richard Branson, Sam Branson and one of our great Paramedics... I wouldn\'t be convinced. <strong>This is the amazing thing about being at the helm of Jigsaw Medical!</strong>\n\nIts been a very busy and sometimes challenging journey so far, but one which I would not change for anything. Since the business was born back in February 2012 we have acquired one of our competitors (and the very first company I worked for), increased the headcount significantly and diversified into a comprehensive service, training and recruitment provider - it is the launch of the latter which will see our new chapter in this amazing journey.\n\nWhilst our Training &amp; Clinical divisions have grown to nearly 5 times the size they were last year, we took an un-missable opportunity to diversify once again into leg 3, of our three leg strategy. The provision of <a href=\"http://recruitment.jigsawmedical.com/\">Locum Doctors</a>, Nurses &amp; Paramedics was already what we did, to a degree, however we did not have a formal, staffing-only service provision available to private hospitals, ambulance trusts or NHS Hospitals... enter, the Jigsaw Medical <a href=\"http://recruitment.jigsawmedical.com\">Recruitment Division</a>.\n\nEach of our three divisions can operate completely independently, but importantly - they can also complement each other entirely. We can recruit, train and deploy staff in one provision, in one business - this is extremely unique.\n\nIn a market worth over £23 billion, it is exciting to expand into recruitment whilst maintaining our patient centred approach. We have recruited an amazing bunch of people to run our recruitment division and I really look forward to growing all three divisions together and welcoming people to #TeamJigsaw in the months &amp; years to come.', 'Growth and Recruitment: A new chaper of Jigsaw Medical', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'growth-recruitment-new-chaper-jigsaw-medical', '', '', '2014-09-07 14:06:44', '2014-09-07 14:06:44', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=525', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(529, 6, '2014-09-08 11:11:42', '2014-09-08 11:11:42', '<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10672308_909261072435284_7317308709202852625_n.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-530\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10672308_909261072435284_7317308709202852625_n.jpg\" alt=\"10672308_909261072435284_7317308709202852625_n\" width=\"315\" height=\"350\" /></a>Those of you who know me will also know that my catch phrases go a little something like... \"It\'s all about the brand\", or \"Get the brand out there\"...</h2>\nI\'m sure people think I am mad, but there is method in my madness! (at least I think there is).\n\nAt the heart of a great business is a first class product or service and every business wants to be a customer’s ‘first choice’. Building and managing a brand can play a large part in making this happen and if you want to strengthen and manage the perceptions of your business, then a strong brand is needed. Good branding elevates and differentiates your like-for-like products or services and gives your customers reason to choose you over your competitors.\n\n<strong>But I\'m a small business, why should I bother?</strong>\n<div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n	<li>The most important reason is that it can help increase your sales. This means that when you need to increase your prices (because you are a small company, and there are only so many hours in the day) then your target audience will be accepting of your price increase. Think about it like this - if your company is built upon a solid brand base, you can build up to the next stage successfully without losing the trust of your customers.</li>\n	<li>Branding also encourages confidence and trust in your product/service - If you do experience a one-off issue with a product or service, your customers would be more likely to understand, if your brand ethos proves that you’ll do what it takes to resolve the problem.</li>\n	<li>Branding also develops the uniqueness of your product.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Trademarks?</strong>\n\nOnce your brand has been born and your clients, staff and stakeholders begin to trust your business, you need to protect it. This is a vital part of a business which many people miss out (including the big companies!). Unless you protect your intellectual property then people can just take it from you and damage that hard work you have put into your brand becoming a trusted and powerful force... <a href=\"http://www.ipo.gov.uk/types/tm.htm\">Find out more about trademarks here</a>\n\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10620589_529819897118201_8065042768012037413_n.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-531 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10620589_529819897118201_8065042768012037413_n.jpg\" alt=\"10620589_529819897118201_8065042768012037413_n\" width=\"296\" height=\"222\" /></a></strong><strong>Getting the brand out there</strong>\n\nIt still amazes me how many companies operate vans with absolutely no branding on at all - that\'s a big area of virtually free advertising not being utilised. At <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> we take our brand under our wing; our ambulances, response cars, support vehicles and training vans are all heavily branded. It doesn\'t stop there, with a powerful social presence and more merchandise than you can shake a stick at. Mugs, coasters, pens and mouse-mats - you name it, we have our logo on it!\n\nMany businesses do not believe in promotional items, however I really do think that if its something people will use and it has your brand and contact details on it - surely it can\'t be a bad idea. You would be amazed how many hospital staff rooms are filled with our bright yellow mugs and matching mouse-mat and coasters!\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>But Remember!</strong></span></h2>\n<p id=\"stcpDiv\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Branding goes way beyond just a logo or a few mugs... When you think about your brand, you really want to think about your entire customer experience…everything from your logo, your website, your social media experiences, the way you answer the phone, to the way your customers experience your staff. Once you have a brand, you need to live up to its expectations and protect it from harm.</strong></span></p>\n\n</div>\n</div>', 'It\'s all about the brand!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'brand', '', '', '2014-09-08 11:11:42', '2014-09-08 11:11:42', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=529', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(533, 6, '2014-09-09 06:35:20', '2014-09-09 06:35:20', '<blockquote>\"Success in business requires discipline and hard work. But if you’re not frightened by these things, the opportunities are just as great today as they ever were.\" – <em>David Rockefeller</em></blockquote>', 'Thought for today - opportunities & success', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'thought-today-opportunities-success', '', '', '2014-09-09 06:35:20', '2014-09-09 06:35:20', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=533', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(535, 6, '2014-09-10 08:04:28', '2014-09-10 08:04:28', '<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/image.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-536\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/image-e1410335388644-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>In my short career outside my own businesses, I have worked in some nice places and some really awful places...</h2>\nIt\'s not all about beanbag rooms, granted - but having a business where people enjoy to come to work, enjoy the environment and contribute to the way in which they work and the environment they do it in. A new member of our team recently said to me that they loved coming to work and worryingly, they also said they have rarely experienced that in the past. I personally love coming to work and I am thrilled that the team do too, I think that\'s what makes us stand out from the crowd.\n<h3>The single most important thing in ANY business, is its people!</h3>\nIt may seem easy to employ people and get them into your team, but you also need to make sure you retain the talent you have managed to acquire and develop. I\'m really proud of the expanding team we are building at <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw</a>, but I am also aware that we need to make sure we stay \'<strong>a great place to work</strong>\'. Now (and as we are growing), we need to keep the team involved in everything we do, whether that be what quotes we have on a new wall, what chairs we have in our board rooms - Jigsaw House is, and needs to continue to be a spectacular and special place to work - one which is unique and difficult to replicate by our competitors.\n<h3>Are we \'a great place to work\'?</h3>\n... I certainly hope so, but one thing I do know is that we come together as a team and plan what to do next to make Jigsaw House and even more amazing place to be.', 'A Great Place To Work', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'great-place-work', '', '', '2014-09-10 08:04:28', '2014-09-10 08:04:28', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=535', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(539, 6, '2014-09-12 16:54:40', '2014-09-12 16:54:40', '[caption id=\"attachment_536\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/image-e1410335388644.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-536\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/image-e1410335388644-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> As our beanbag room suggests... \"it\'s about being different\"![/caption]\n\n<strong>It’s not about ‘emulation’ or ‘following suit’…</strong> Copying an existing business will not work – unless you take the bits they are not doing well and make those same \'bits\' better in your business. There is a strong case for not re-inventing the wheel and I totally agree with this, but why mirror an imperfect business model when you can innovate and improve it, making it even better!?\n\nThere are thousands of businesses doing the same thing we do in the three divisions we cover in Jigsaw Medical, all over the UK…\n\n<strong>So why are we succeeding?</strong>\n\nWe have simply taken what the industry doesn’t do very well, and made it 10 times better. For example in the £23 billion market that is recruitment, there are many small and large players – but as an innovative and positive business - ran by clinicians, we know what the rest do well and what they don’t do well. We listen to our locums and make Jigsaw Medical the place they want to commit to, bend over backwards for and have a lot of fun being a part of.\n\nIt\'s about having the right people, doing the right jobs and empowering them enough so they stand out to other employers, but treating them so they won\'t want to! Business leaders often forget about the people who help them to succeed, it\'s the leading cause of attrition in high-performing teams and specifically key team members... Be careful, if you operate like this, not only would nobody want to copy your business, there is often a competitor with the right qualities waiting in the sidelines!\n\nDon’t just copy someone else’s business, take the industry by the reins, and <strong>make it better! </strong>\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Remember</span>: “it’s about being different”</h2>', 'It\'s not about \'emulation\' or \'following suit\'...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'emulation-following-suit', '', '', '2014-09-12 16:54:40', '2014-09-12 16:54:40', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=539', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(547, 6, '2014-09-17 15:28:33', '2014-09-17 15:28:33', '<header>\n<h2>Jigsaw Medical wins the Lloyds Enterprise Awards, Best Enterprise (North!)</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10646649_539321952834662_6666074932913259183_n.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-549\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10646649_539321952834662_6666074932913259183_n-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"10646649_539321952834662_6666074932913259183_n\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nOut of the three categories open to entrepreneurs currently studying at universities across England and Wales – or who graduated within the past five years and have been trading for more than one year. The Best Enterprise award goes to the business which has been running for over two years and demonstrates innovation, as well as showing real potential to grow over the next five years to become a recognised business within its respective sector… <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> are proud to have won Best Enterprise in the Northern heats! As part of the award, Jigsaw will receive a cash investment of £5,000. One-to-one local business mentoring will also be available to prize winners.\n\n</header>Winning the Best Enterprise in the North is an exceptional achievement for the whole team at Jigsaw Medical, it provides recognition of our ethos as a business and our staggering growth, which is this year set to be over 400% on last years figures. We are determined to make Jigsaw a great place to work and develop the business as a team and we look forward to competing in the National awards in October!\n\n<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10628536_539393416160849_8752311288722433342_n.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-548\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/10628536_539393416160849_8752311288722433342_n-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"10628536_539393416160849_8752311288722433342_n\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>Myself and the team at Jigsaw Medical, along with the winners of the other 4 national heats, will qualify for the national award of Best Enterprise at the Grand Final in Edgbaston on October 15, where they will be judged by an expert business panel including Tim Campbell, former Apprentice winner and founder of the Bright Ideas Trust.\n\nThe overall Best Enterprise Award winner will receive £50,000 to invest in their business and will also benefit from an additional 2 hour mentoring session with senior executives from Lloyds Banking Group.', 'Lloyds Enterprise Awards... North Heat', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lloyds-enterprise-awards-north-heat', '', '', '2014-09-17 15:28:33', '2014-09-17 15:28:33', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=547', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(551, 6, '2014-09-18 12:14:17', '2014-09-18 12:14:17', '<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/solicitors.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-552 alignright\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/solicitors-300x197.jpg\" alt=\"solicitors\" width=\"300\" height=\"197\" /></a>In business you are likely to require legal advice from time-to-time... it\'s a fact of life in a commercial world...</h2>\nGetting the right advice, from the right solicitors is key when moving forward and protecting your business. Over the last couple of years, during the (thankfully rare) legal matters we have had to either defend or address - we have obtained a great pool of legal firms in order to protect our brand and commercial interests, we have built solid relationships with them and ensure they are ready to act, should this be required.... it also helps that my girlfriend is in the legal world - but she would probably disagree, and for that reason, we don\'t engage with her professional services directly (but its a perfect place for quick and comparitive advice)!\n\nI remember the very first \'legal letter\' I got at aged just 14. It was regarding my \'next big thing\' which, during my naive, younger years - got me into a bit of bother (although it did fizzle out when they realised, at the time, all I had was a laptop and a skateboard). The law firm in question specialises in Intellectual Property Law, the letter was fantastically written and so much so, you can guess who we now use for our IP legal requirements now?!\n\nIt\'s amazing really, the bigger your brand &amp; company gets and the more of a commercial threat it poses to your competitors - the more legal correspondence which is required, not just that - the more you need protect your brand (though trademarks etc - see <a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/brand/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>) the more legal input will be required. Although this is not a scientific calculation, I am sure you can imagine their rationale. I guess the truth is, they should be reading my article on: \"<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/concentrate-on-you/\">Concentrating on your business, not your competitors</a>\"\n\nBut seriously, having the right legal advisers not only protects your business, but also ensures your approach to legal matters is professional and above all - accurate. We have previously received some terribly written, infactual and very unprofessional \'high street\' Solicitors letters - so you can imagine how that reflects on those concerned on the \'other side of the fence\'.\n\n<strong>Some top tips when selecting your business\' Solicitors....</strong>\n<div>\n<ul>\n	<li>Make sure you are clear and focused about what you are trying to achieve so you don’t waste your time and money.</li>\n	<li>Before you make any appointments, talk to three or four different firms – you’ll want information about charges, how they handle the longer term adviser/client relationship if that’s relevant - and anything else that is important to you, such as whether they are willing to come and see you in your own workplace.</li>\n	<li>Look at their qualifications – what they are, what they mean; ask how long the firm has been in business, <strong>and what your adviser specialises in</strong>! (having a high-street \'generalist\' lawyer dealing, for example, with your employment law matters is simply not good!)</li>\n	<li>Do they talk to you in plain English or are they using jargon terms that you don’t understand?</li>\n	<li>Solicitors should have a practising certificate, which tells you they are fully qualified and insured, which most display in their offices.  If you have any concerns, you can check with the <a href=\"http://www.sra.org.uk/home/home.page\">Solicitors Regulatory Authority</a>.</li>\n	<li><strong>and Finally...</strong><strong> Don\'t be afraid of spending money on senior Partners and highly-commended Solicitors, at the end of the day - it is your business you are protecting.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'Getting The Right Advice...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'getting-right-advice', '', '', '2014-09-18 12:14:17', '2014-09-18 12:14:17', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=551', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(555, 2, '2010-09-10 07:24:14', '2010-09-10 14:24:14', '[gallery]\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n\nYou can use this page to test the Theme\'s handling of the[gallery]\n\nshortcode, including the <code>columns</code> parameter, from 1 to 9 columns. Themes are only required to support the default setting (3 columns), so this page is entirely optional.\n<h2>One Column</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"1\"]\n<h2>Two Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"2\"]\n<h2>Three Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"3\"]\n<h2>Four Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"4\"]\n<h2>Five Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"5\"]\n<h2>Six Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"6\"]\n<h2>Seven Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"7\"]\n<h2>Eight Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"8\"]\n<h2>Nine Columns</h2>\n[gallery columns=\"9\"]', 'Post Format: Gallery', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-gallery__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:10', '2017-05-19 10:12:10', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=555', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(559, 2, '2010-05-09 07:51:54', '2010-05-09 14:51:54', '“I never tried to prove nothing, just wanted to give a good show. My life has always been my music, it\'s always come first, but the music ain\'t worth nothing if you can\'t lay it on the public. The main thing is to live for that audience, \'cause what you\'re there for is to please the people.”', 'Post Format: Aside', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-aside__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=559', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(562, 2, '2010-01-08 07:59:31', '2010-01-08 14:59:31', 'Abbott: Strange as it may seem, they give ball players nowadays very peculiar names.\n\nCostello: Funny names?\n\nAbbott: Nicknames, nicknames. Now, on the St. Louis team we have Who\'s on first, What\'s on second, I Don\'t Know is on third--\n\nCostello: That\'s what I want to find out. I want you to tell me the names of the fellows on the St. Louis team.\n\nAbbott: I\'m telling you. Who\'s on first, What\'s on second, I Don\'t Know is on third--\n\nCostello: You know the fellows\' names?\n\nAbbott: Yes.\n\nCostello: Well, then who\'s playing first?\n\nAbbott: Yes.\n\nCostello: I mean the fellow\'s name on first base.\n\nAbbott: Who.\n\nCostello: The fellow playin\' first base.\n\nAbbott: Who.\n\nCostello: The guy on first base.\n\nAbbott: Who is on first.\n\nCostello: Well, what are you askin\' me for?\n\nAbbott: I\'m not asking you--I\'m telling you. Who is on first.\n\nCostello: I\'m asking you--who\'s on first?\n\nAbbott: That\'s the man\'s name.\n\nCostello: That\'s who\'s name?\n\nAbbott: Yes.\n\nCostello: When you pay off the first baseman every month, who gets the money?\n\nAbbott: Every dollar of it. And why not, the man\'s entitled to it.\n\nCostello: Who is?\n\nAbbott: Yes.\n\nCostello: So who gets it?\n\nAbbott: Why shouldn\'t he? Sometimes his wife comes down and collects it.\n\nCostello: Who\'s wife?\n\nAbbott: Yes. After all, the man earns it.\n\nCostello: Who does?\n\nAbbott: Absolutely.\n\nCostello: Well, all I\'m trying to find out is what\'s the guy\'s name on first base?\n\nAbbott: Oh, no, no. What is on second base.\n\nCostello: I\'m not asking you who\'s on second.\n\nAbbott: Who\'s on first!\n\nCostello: St. Louis has a good outfield?\n\nAbbott: Oh, absolutely.\n\nCostello: The left fielder\'s name?\n\nAbbott: Why.\n\nCostello: I don\'t know, I just thought I\'d ask.\n\nAbbott: Well, I just thought I\'d tell you.\n\nCostello: Then tell me who\'s playing left field?\n\nAbbott: Who\'s playing first.\n\nCostello: Stay out of the infield! The left fielder\'s name?\n\nAbbott: Why.\n\nCostello: Because.\n\nAbbott: Oh, he\'s center field.\n\nCostello: Wait a minute. You got a pitcher on this team?\n\nAbbott: Wouldn\'t this be a fine team without a pitcher?\n\nCostello: Tell me the pitcher\'s name.\n\nAbbott: Tomorrow.\n\nCostello: Now, when the guy at bat bunts the ball--me being a good catcher--I want to throw the guy out at first base, so I pick up the ball and throw it to who?\n\nAbbott: Now, that\'s he first thing you\'ve said right.\n\nCostello: I DON\'T EVEN KNOW WHAT I\'M TALKING ABOUT!\n\nAbbott: Don\'t get excited. Take it easy.\n\nCostello: I throw the ball to first base, whoever it is grabs the ball, so the guy runs to second. Who picks up the ball and throws it to what. What throws it to I don\'t know. I don\'t know throws it back to tomorrow--a triple play.\n\nAbbott: Yeah, it could be.\n\nCostello: Another guy gets up and it\'s a long ball to center.\n\nAbbott: Because.\n\nCostello: Why? I don\'t know. And I don\'t care.\n\nAbbott: What was that?\n\nCostello: I said, I DON\'T CARE!\n\nAbbott: Oh, that\'s our shortstop!', 'Post Format: Chat', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-chat__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:12', '2017-05-19 10:12:12', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=562', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(565, 2, '2010-03-07 08:06:53', '2010-03-07 15:06:53', '<a href=\"http://make.wordpress.org/themes\" title=\"The WordPress Theme Review Team Website\">The WordPress Theme Review Team Website</a>', 'Post Format: Link', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-link__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=565', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(567, 6, '2014-10-17 16:43:07', '2014-10-17 16:43:07', '<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Screen-Shot-2014-10-17-at-17.06.54.png\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-569\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Screen-Shot-2014-10-17-at-17.06.54-300x214.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2014-10-17 at 17.06.54\" width=\"300\" height=\"214\" /></a>Following our success in winning the Northern heats of the Lloyds Bank Enterprise Awards we were invited to the Grand Final...</h2>\nAlthough Jigsaw Medical didn\'t bag the \'grand final prize\', settling with the \'Best Enterprise - North\' award is something I am immensely proud of the team for and whilst sat with some very inspirational people (which I will come to later), I had time to reflect on where we have been and where we have come...\n\nIt seems like only a matter of weeks ago that I was sat with my parents deciding on what to call, what would become \'<a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a>\' and persuading them that the \'pocket money\' I would earn from, at the time, doing event first aid cover, would outweigh the costs of a vehicle, the numerous insurances etc. But as business owners themselves, they fully supported me and helped me get in contact with insurance companies and even (with a slight bending of the ear), let me use one of their company vans! - I must have forgotten to tell them at the time, but I planned on converting into an Ambulance response car - much to their delight on its return from the conversion company! (but that\'s history... I hope).\n\nWhilst I was sat amongst senior executives from Lloyds Bank, CEO\'s of multi-national companies and inspiring business leaders, I had time to reflect on what Jigsaw Medical has \'grown up to be\'. I was sat there with my Parents and Sammie (my girlfriend) and numerous people wanted to hear all about the business, which was fine, because I can talk about it all day!!\n\n<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/teamjigsaw.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-568 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/teamjigsaw.png\" alt=\"teamjigsaw\" width=\"357\" height=\"238\" /></a>Sat on the \'Jigsaw Medical table\' was <a href=\"http://www.tonyrobinsonobe.co.uk/\">Tony Robbinson OBE</a>, not only was he such a gent and such an inspiring chap, it was an absolute pleasure to be in his company, hear his stories and experiences. <a href=\"http://www.tim-campbell.co.uk/\">Tim Campbell MBE</a> was also judging the final and it was amazing to hear his story and experience his frankly awesome speech! - I was humbled to be amongst some inspirational and amazing people, something I had not experienced before - with the \'spotlight\' being on us.\n\nBut it was this that made me realise something.... the journey I had embarked upon in February 2012 had brought me to that position, sat on that table, surrounded by \'Jigsaw Medical\' branding, a 6-foot high picture of my face (which they must have forgotten to tell me about!). Not to mention being in the company of two legends such as Tony, Tim and the amazing judges. But it\'s not that which really made me reflect on where we are today. Although I had the pleasure of being there and pitching the company to these influential and powerful people, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>It is not me</strong></span> who has simply landed there by mistake (or at least I hope not) and certainly not single-handedly, its the teamwork and the amazing people we have on-board the Jigsaw journey that has got us there, it just happens to be me who founded the business and has the pleasure to lead the team. I knew that already, but when you reflect on how far the team has come, it\'s pretty amazing!! We call these people #TeamJigsaw and it includes everyone, our Locum Doctors and Nurses, event Paramedics, sales team, office team, recruitment team, first aiders and the team in FM - absolutely <strong>everyone</strong> involved in the business as a whole. It is these people who determine its success, not me.\n\nWith all of the growth and concentration in the entire team, I wouldn\'t say \"I didn\'t know how far we have come\", but I certainly didn\'t appreciate our collective success, as an entire team and when I compare it to where we were just 12 months ago, with 300% growth a successful acquisition and a rapidly growing team!\n<h3>Tim, Tony and the whole experience of the Enterprise Awards made me reflect and really put our achievements so far into perspective, so I suppose all that would be left to say is....</h3>\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>Thank You</em> to the awesome #TeamJigsaw!</span> - Here\'s to the next part of the journey....</h2>', 'The Journey So Far - A Moment Of Reflection & Teamwork!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'journey-far-moment-reflection-teamwork', '', '', '2014-10-17 16:43:07', '2014-10-17 16:43:07', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=567', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(568, 2, '2010-08-06 08:09:39', '2010-08-06 15:09:39', '[caption id=\"attachment_612\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"640\" caption=\"Chunk of resinous blackboy husk, Clarkson, Western Australia. This burns like a spinifex log.\"]<a href=\"http://wpthemetestdata.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/dsc20040724_152504_532.jpg\"><img src=\"http://wpthemetestdata.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/dsc20040724_152504_532.jpg\" alt=\"chunk of resinous blackboy husk\" title=\"dsc20040724_152504_532\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" class=\"size-full wp-image-612\" /></a>[/caption]\n', 'Post Format: Image (Linked)', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-image-linked__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=568', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(575, 2, '2010-02-05 08:13:15', '2010-02-05 15:13:15', '<blockquote>Only one thing is impossible for God: To find any sense in any copyright law on the planet.\n<cite><a href=\"http://www.brainyquote.com/quotes/quotes/m/marktwain163473.html\">Mark Twain</a></cite></blockquote>', 'Post Format: Quote', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-quote__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=575', 0, 'post', '', 0),
