(587, 2, '2010-07-02 08:36:44', '2010-07-02 15:36:44', 'Link:\n\n<a href=\"http://wpthemetestdata.files.wordpress.com/2008/06/originaldixielandjazzbandwithalbernard-stlouisblues.mp3\">St. Louis Blues</a>\n\nAudio shortcode:\n\n[audio http://wpthemetestdata.files.wordpress.com/2008/06/originaldixielandjazzbandwithalbernard-stlouisblues.mp3]', 'Post Format: Audio', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'post-format-audio__trashed', '', '', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '2017-05-19 10:12:11', '', 0, 'http://wpthemetestdata.wordpress.com/?p=587', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(592, 6, '2014-11-16 13:20:03', '2014-11-16 13:20:03', '<h3>I must say, I didn\'t think I would be writing about an office in Australia for some years yet, but it is testament to the team at <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com\">Jigsaw Medical</a> that we have managed to make this bold move so soon in our journey..<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/sydney_harbour.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-593\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/sydney_harbour-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"sydney_harbour\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a></h3>\nGranted, we are not the first recruitment agency, training company or clinical provider who has made such a move. However, we will be the only UK based agency dealing with Paramedics internationally, on this scale. Our aim is to use this new brand (Jigsaw Medical Global) and our presence in Australia to drive recruitment in and out of the UK, with offshore and onshore opportunities already available globally. It has been an amazing journey, especially given that I only actual finished university and became a full-time member of the team, just 16 months ago! The markets in all three divisions of our business are saturated, but I have learn\'t over this short space of time, that it really doesn\'t matter - <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">providing what you are doing is different</span> (those of you who have been to Jigsaw House will have seen quotes to this effect all over the walls!).\n\nThe whole team at Jigsaw Medical are so pleased to have made this positive and forward thinking move, we are uniquely placed to recruit, train and deploy heath-care staff across our three divisions; something that to our knowledge, has never been done before. It is an absolute credit to our team that we have got to this point so quickly and we are really looking forward to developing our Global team at our Sydney office and beyond…\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTo find out more about Jigsaw Medical Global, visit our dedicated website <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedicalglobal.com\">www.jigsawmedicalglobal.com</a>.', 'An office in Sydney... now I didn\'t expect to be saying that just 2 years into the journey!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'office-sydney-now-didnt-expect-saying-just-2-years-journey', '', '', '2014-11-16 13:20:03', '2014-11-16 13:20:03', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=592', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(595, 6, '2014-11-16 13:25:09', '2014-11-16 13:25:09', '', 'Business Is All About People...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'business-people', '', '', '2014-11-16 13:25:09', '2014-11-16 13:25:09', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=595', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(600, 6, '2014-12-22 17:08:28', '2014-12-22 17:08:28', '<h2>The first time I had the chance to really stop and think about where we have come in 2014 was when designing the front cover of our annual review...</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-22-at-16.18.16.png\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-601 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-22-at-16.18.16-218x300.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2014-12-22 at 16.18.16\" width=\"218\" height=\"300\" /></a>I found myself looking through the Jigsaw Medical Facebook pictures to design an eye catching cover for our 2014 Annual Report, the first of its kind since the beginnings of Jigsaw Medical. With pictures of our team with <a href=\"http://www.virgin.com/richard-branson\">Richard Branson</a> and Sam Branson at the <a href=\"https://www.strivechallenge.com/\">Virgin STRIVE Challenge</a>, images from the \'Tour de France\' and of our ambulances queuing up outside A&amp;E departments on 999 work with various trusts.\n\nIt was at this point that I was able to stop and reflect, I wouldn\'t say I forgot about everything we have done this year, but rather that we were too busy on the very fast road of growth to do so. (something I\'m sure I will set as a goal for 2015, so I do more of it!). Nonetheless this urged me to send an email to the team across our three offices to thank them for their efforts in 2014 and highlight some of the amazing things that we, together, have achieved. I would like to think I give thanks to the team very regularly, but the realisation of what we have achieved holistically is something easily forgotten in this fast-pace environment we have created.\n\nI remember just 12 months ago, sitting with my family at the Blackhouse Grill in Chester, discussing my (at the time) rather ambitious vision for Jigsaw Medical. I distinctly remember saying <em>\"I would love to be sat here in a few years seeing a Jigsaw Medical ambulance driving past the window, on a 999 call\"</em>. Strangely, last Friday I was sat in this same restaurant with some of the team from Jigsaw Medical, celebrating our achievements in 2014. Just 12 months on, that goal became a reality as \'JA603\', one of our Emergency Ambulances drove past whilst on contract with the local NHS Ambulance Service... for me that was a huge moment and something which will stick with me forever, there was a moment of madness in the restaurant as the team saw one of our own driving past! It may seem a bit cheesy, but there is absolutely nothing like the feeling of hitting these goals, especially when you least expect it!\n<h4>So... Jigsaw Medical in 2014 - A Review...</h4>\n<a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/2014-@-Jigsaw.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1151\" src=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/2014-@-Jigsaw.jpg\" alt=\"Processed with Moldiv\" width=\"259\" height=\"260\" /></a><strong>A <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/blog/jigsaw-medical-2014-review/\">recent blog entry from Neil Coleman</a>, our social media &amp; PR guru summarised things nicely! I have taken some key bits from his post...</strong>\n\nWhat a year it’s been at Jigsaw Medical. Unrivalled growth, exciting event coverage, overseas expansion, laughs, tears and everything that comes along with being part of one of the UK’s leading and most innovative medical recruitment, clinical and training companies. 2014 saw the establishment of a new <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/recruitment/\">recruitment division</a> that offers a formal, staffing-only service provision available to private hospitals, ambulance trusts and NHS hospitals.\n\nIt has also been a particularly exciting year for our <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/home.html\">clinical division</a>, as Jigsaw provided medical cover not only for traditional ambulance settings but also for:\n<ul>\n	<li>Virgin STRIVE challenge – providing a medical team for 10 people who ran, rowed, cycled, hiked and climbed from the O2 arena in London to the peak of the Matterhorn in Switzerland.</li>\n	<li>Tour de France Grand Départ – supporting the first aid providers, NHS ambulance services and event medical management company with the provision of 227 paramedics, nurses and doctors throughout the 2 days.</li>\n	<li>The Big Reunion, UK’s Biggest Winter Music Festival – providing comprehensive medical services and treatment for all festival goers.</li>\n	<li>Various NHS 999 Contracts - supporting NHS trusts with emergency 999 calls, accross the UK.</li>\n</ul>\n<a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jigsaw-Medical-Global-Glow-Bg.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-968\" src=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jigsaw-Medical-Global-Glow-Bg.png\" alt=\"Jigsaw-Medical-Global-Glow-Bg\" width=\"277\" height=\"72\" /></a>2014 also saw the creation of <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedicalglobal.com/\">Jigsaw Medical Global</a>. This expansion has seen the Jigsaw Medical brand go to Sydney, Australia to become the only UK based agency to deal with paramedics internationally on this scale. The aim is to use this opportunity to drive recruitment in and out of the UK, with offshore and onshore opportunities already available to UK based candidates and global candidates.\n\n<strong>All of the above has contributed to a 350% growth in comparison to where we were in 2013 so we’d like to say a massive thank you and congratulations to everyone at #TeamJigsaw for a fantastic 2014.</strong>\n<h3>2014 In Summary</h3>\nI think it is safe to say that we as a team are as shocked as everyone else to see where we have come, although it has taken a considerable amount of effort from the entire team to get it right. We needed to ensure we kept delivering the same, clinically focused service to our clients and patients is something we made a priority at every step. To be honest, I personally feel that having the right people on-board, improving our service delivery and clinical focus has resulted in much of this staggering growth.\n\nOur growth has also seen a 300% increase in the size of our full-time office &amp; training team, with over 2,000 candidates joining #TeamJigsaw over the last few months. We took some bold steps for a young company in 2014, but we have done it with the right support and the right people on board, from our appointment of our Finance Director, to ensure the growth is financially sustainable and our Medical Director, to ensure it is clinically appropriate. Not to mention those with a wealth of experience to drive us forward strategically, including <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/blog/jms-appoints-laurie-percival-as-non-executive-director/\">Laurie Percival</a> who came to us from her position as CEO of a £500 million recruitment brand.\n\nI am convinced the single reason for our growth and success in 2014 is <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/our-people.html\">our people</a>, who we like to call #TeamJigsaw! - <strong>So thank you to everyone who has helped make this year so successful!</strong>\n<h3>What to Expect in 2015?</h3>\nNeedless to say, we have a plan. However, our plan for this year has been exceeded more than three times over - so who knows what to expect. However, what I will say is that it will see more amazing people join #TeamJigsaw and we hope to increase revenue and profits by some 500%, largely down to our sustained growth &amp; innovation across the three divisions within the business. We will have more shifts for locum workers, more courses in our training division, lots more clinical service provision to events, private &amp; NHS clients, and international opportunities for UK Paramedics - to name a few.\n\nIn a nutshell we want to continue on from 2014 with a vision to \'revamping\' the UK medical recruitment market, continuing to innovate and develop in our Clinical &amp; Training divisions. I truly believe we have a unique model with the very best team, something which I can see being very powerful and pioneering in 2015, and beyond.\n<h3>I will leave you with this thought...</h3>\nI love quotes and those of you who have visited us at Jigsaw House will know that (they are all over the walls). The most recent of which is a selection for my new office, for example one from Walt Disney - \"If you can dream it, you can do it\"....\n\n<strong>...However more prudent to this blog post, another reads....</strong>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/4d3c1c5bf36fa.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-605\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/4d3c1c5bf36fa.jpg\" alt=\"4d3c1c5bf36fa\" width=\"600\" height=\"445\" /></a>Merry Christmas &amp; Happy New Year... Here\'s to 2015!</h2>', '2014... From the Tour de France, to the Matterhorn, to Australia - What a year it\'s been!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2014-tour-de-france-matterhorn-australia-year', '', '', '2014-12-22 17:08:28', '2014-12-22 17:08:28', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=600', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(612, 6, '2014-12-29 17:50:26', '2014-12-29 17:50:26', '<h3><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/141112_goals.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-613\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/141112_goals.jpg\" alt=\"141112_goals\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></a></h3>\n<h3>One of the quotes in my office is from Walt Disney and it reads: \"If you can dream it, you can do it\"... but how do dreamers become doers?...</h3>\nGranted, it is true that the \'doing\' part of this statement is the harder part of the two, but I strongly believe that the above quote is very true. Most of the time, it is the fear of failure or \'not knowing where to start\' which stops entrepreneurs from \'doing\' rather than \'dreaming\'!\n<h3>Some top tips which might just help you to turn your dreams into reality!</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Have goals! - </strong>You should have goals, whether they are just a goal for Monday, a goal for the month or a goal further ahead… You need them to be the first thing you do on your quest to develop your dream into reality! Don’t forget – if your goal involves your team (which I’m sure it will), you need to share it with them, so they can also focus on helping you reach it!</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Surround yourself with doers, not dreamers -</strong>  I think it is safe to say everyone has dreams, but make sure you are surrounding yourself with positive, like-minded people - particularly if they themselves have turned some of their dreams into reality, they will no doubt have some pointers for you from their journey.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Nothing is impossible! - </strong>If you think your goal is out of reach, think again. Whilst I wouldn\'t encourage anyone to try and beat Richard Branson into space tourism with a start-up business, you should work towards milestones to ultimately get you to the main goal. Be realistic, but don\'t make it easily achievable - that\'s boring!<strong>\n</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Be better -</strong> Take some time to sit down &amp; figure out how your biggest competitor is promoting their brand &amp; plan something smarter &amp; more creative for yours... Don\'t re-invent the wheel without being creative!</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Will it work!?</h3>\n... If everyone knew the answer to that question, we would all be very successful in everything we wanted to do... But I do believe, nothing is impossible if you have the right people and the right formula.', 'How Dreamers Can Become Doers...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dreamers-can-become-doers', '', '', '2014-12-29 17:50:26', '2014-12-29 17:50:26', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=612', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(617, 6, '2014-12-30 10:27:49', '2014-12-30 10:27:49', '<h3><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Customer-Service-on-Twitter-sorry.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-618\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Customer-Service-on-Twitter-sorry.png\" alt=\"Customer-Service-on-Twitter-sorry\" width=\"540\" height=\"301\" /></a></h3>\n<h3>Many businesses are turning to Twitter and other social media platforms for their customer service, are you Tweeting back?</h3>\nI\'m sure that I\'m not the only person who turns to Twitter, Facebook or finding the CEO on Linkedin when I have a query or problem? People often want instant responses to their customer service queries, not emails which often take 24hrs to respond to! I think it\'s safe to say that social media has a massive impact on how a company is perceived to the public, especially the response time from Tweets, whether that\'s a rare complaint, question or sales enquiry. So much so, many businesses (including Jigsaw Medical) employ dedicated people in their teams to manage their social media requirements (our is <a href=\"http://www.jigsawmedical.com/blog/jigsaw-medical-appoints-social-media-pr-intern/\">Neil Coleman</a>, who looks more like Olly Murs!).\n\nI recently had a positive experience of social media based customer support with <a href=\"http://www.londonmidland.com/\">London Midland Trains </a>and whilst they couldn\'t rectify the issue, the response from them via Twitter was both speedy and appropriate. Other great examples comes from some of our suppliers, such as <a href=\"http://www.ukfast.co.uk\">UKFast</a> and our clients, including the many <a href=\"http://www.virgin.com\">Virgin</a> brands you see around the world - they all seem to have exceptional Twitter interaction &amp; support!\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/social-channles-image-01.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-621\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/social-channles-image-01-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"social-channles-image-01\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" /></a>Why should your business use Social Media?...</h3>\nThere still seems to be a clear split between businesses and indeed the people within them as to their view on how businesses should use social media. Many see employing people to manage social media as a strange move - but I can assure you it\'s not! Here are some top reasons why you should be using social media:\n\n<strong>Customer Service -</strong> This is the  main reason why you should use social media for your business. You will be able to connect with your customers because they themselves are using it. Specifically Twitter has become a daily routine for many consumers and businesses alike, if you have an unsatisfied customer you are likely to hear from them on twitter (whether or not your company has a presence!). Surely it\'s better to manage their feedback publicly on Twitter, rather than not know about it at all!?\n\n<strong>Branding -</strong> You don’t have to be a big brand like Google or Starbucks to brand yourself on social media channels. For many, the use of Twitter, Linkedin and Facebook is an opportunity to re-enforce the brand and what better for a huge advertising platform than this! Many businesses (including Jigsaw Medical, which is why you are reading this) also have their Directors or leaders on Twitter and other social platforms.\n\n<strong>News - </strong>Social media is also a great platform to share your news with your followers and keep them updated with the latest \'happenings\' in your organisation.\n\n<strong>\"It\'s gone viral!\"</strong> - If you have succeeded gaining some popularity with your social media accounts you will know how viral they can be. This will be part of your marketing strategies that you can use in the future. Hey, it worked for Justin Beiber! - just think of social media as a free advertising platform.\n\n<strong>Willingness to act</strong> - I personally think this is the single most important reason your business should use Social Media. If you allow yourself to be potentially exposed on social media, with the correct management this can be seen extremely positively by your clients. This shows willingness and transparency, reassuring your customers that you are willing to act on peoples concerns or feedback.\n\n<strong>Everyone\'s doing it!</strong> - The guy who runs the local sweet shop down the road. The landscape architect. The shoe shop owner. And lots of big companies, such as Dell, HP, 02 and Microsoft. Having your business on Twitter is seen as a must.\n<h3>The golden rules...<a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/golden-rules.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-622\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/golden-rules.png\" alt=\"golden-rules\" width=\"700\" height=\"200\" /></a></h3>\n<strong>1. If your going to do it, do it properly! </strong>- Don\'t fall into the trap of thinking social media is a great idea for your business, setting up your Facebook page, Twitter account and Linkedin company page - then leaving it for 12-months post-less! Unmanaged social media accounts are bad news and when your latest customer searches your company name on social media channels and sees the inactivity - it looks worse than not being on social media at all! No matter how small your business, as a minimum you should aim to do at least one tweet, Facebook and LinkedIn post, each week. If you don\'t have time to do this, there are lots of web and marketing company\'s who can manage this on you behalf for little cost, but remember, it\'s always better coming from you.\n\n<strong>2. Whilst your at it, get the boss on too</strong> - Whether your organisation is large or small, professional accounts for the leaders, founders and Directors can also work in your company\'s favor. I am on Twitter, Facebook and Linkedin and I often get queries direct to my account, rather than the companies. This again shows <span class=\"st\">transparency</span> and allows people to really become involved and get a complete view of the organisation holistically. Whilst this isn\'t for everyone, I really enjoy the feedback from our clients and team on social media and it\'s something which allows me to be easily accessible if someone does have an issue.\n\n<strong>3. Think before you Tweet </strong>- Having been here myself on a number of occasions it can often be too easy to respond in a confrontational way if someone (such as a competitor) is being less than polite about your business on social media. This is one of the reasons why Neil manages Jigsaw Medical\'s social media, he is a professional and ensures our responses as a company are both appropriate, yet professional. My advice is to take 10 minutes before replying and I can assure you the words you chose in your response will be very different. Just remember, once its on social media, its on for life - whether you delete it or not, the damage is often done.\n\n<strong>4. Set goals</strong> - Yes, I\'m always squeezing this one in... but goals can apply to anything. For example, your goal could be to gain 500 followers on Twitter in the first six months, so set this and monitor it. The great thing about social media is that you can share these goals with your audience. One great example of this was when I recently provided an opportunity for one of my followers on Twitter to win a famous Jigsaw Medical bobble hat! This worked really well and I hit the target of reaching 40,000 followers that day. Be creative and engage your followers as much as you can.\n\n<strong>5. It\'s not just about numbers - </strong>Don\'t get yourself bogged down with how many followers you do or don\'t have, concentrate on those you do have, engage with them and make them feel part of your journey. Don’t try to follow 10,000 people straight away. You’ll just come across as a spammer. There is no value in a multitude of followers or \'likes\' if they don’t really care about what you have to say. It’s about conversations, relationships and engagement, not the masses. Build your “network” gradually and consistently. Be selective, be targeted, and be clear on what your objectives are.\n<h3>Whats next?</h3>\nIf you haven\'t already, get your social media accounts setup and start engaging with your customers!', 'Turning to Twitter for Customer Service...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'turning-twitter-customer-service', '', '', '2014-12-30 10:27:49', '2014-12-30 10:27:49', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=617', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(629, 6, '2015-01-22 08:58:37', '2015-01-22 08:58:37', '<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/index.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-630 size-full\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/index.jpg\" alt=\"index\" width=\"224\" height=\"192\" /></a>January is often the month where people kick off the plan for the year ahead and set their goals on track...</h2>\nFirstly, you should remember that a business may at first be the vision of just one person, but soon becomes the vision of the whole team of people you employ or involve in your business. <strong>So rule number one; let your team come up with the goals as well as you! </strong>If your business culture is similar to Jigsaw\'s the business is as much your teams as it is yours.\n\nI am a keen believer in goals and lining up a target, this goes for business and personal life. My business goals come in all shapes and sizes and focus on different aspects of my businesses. At the beginning of the year it is important to lay some foundation goals - where do you want to get to that year?, where do your team what to get to? and importantly make them measurable, objective and realistic (although #TeamJigsaw would tell you mine are often very ambitious!).\n<h2>Involve your team</h2>\nI know I am repeating myself here. But don’t forget, your goals with invariably involve your team, so you need to share it with them and involve them in the goal setting process, so they can also focus on helping you reach it! Don’t just keep it to yourself!\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/10868092_989236447771079_4293696508673558744_n.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-631 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/10868092_989236447771079_4293696508673558744_n-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"10868092_989236447771079_4293696508673558744_n\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>Sit back before you set...</h2>\nI recently went away skiing at the beginning of January and something I have picked up from <a href=\"http://www.lawrencejones.eu\">Lawrence Jones MBE</a> is that taking time out to look at the bigger picture is vital (something it took me a while to get the hang of). You would be amazed what spending time on the mountains with your family can spark in your goal setting and even thought process - try it!\n\nToday I have the first board meeting of the year and in the \'upside down management\' structure we have in Jigsaw Medical - the goals have already been set, the team have come together and made a plan for 2015, so lets hope its an awesome one.\n<h2>Some personal goals...</h2>\nAs well as the goals for the business (which you should share), I think its also important to have some personal goals to keep yourself motivated. They can be kept to yourself or shared with your friends, family or colleagues... Here are a couple of mine:\n<ul>\n	<li>To visit <a href=\"http://www.virginlimitededition.com/en/necker-island\">Necker Island</a> at some point in 2015</li>\n	<li>To make in profit, what we generated in revenue in 2014 (this is a personal one as its one of those \'ambitious ones\' I spoke of. However, we did do this in 2014, so nothing is impossible!)</li>\n	<li>To further support start-up businesses, just like I was in February 2012</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>... so what are your goals for 2015?</h2>', 'Setting Goals for 2015...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'setting-goals-2015', '', '', '2015-01-22 08:58:37', '2015-01-22 08:58:37', '', 0, 'http://www.chrispercival.co.uk/?p=629', 0, 'post', '', 0);
